'''
Create a program that simulates the operation of an ATM. At the beginning, ask the user what the
VALUE TO BE WITHDRAWN (integer number) and the program will inform how many bills of each value will be delivered.

NOTE: Consider that the cashier has bills of: 50, 20, 10 and 1
'''

print('ATM')
print('Available notes: 50, 20, 10, 1')

saque = int(input('What amount do you want to withdraw?: '))
valor_saque = saque

notas_50 = saque // 50
saque %= 50

notas_20 = saque // 20
saque %= 20

notas_10 = saque // 10
saque %= 10

notas_1 = saque

print(f'To withdraw the value {valor_saque} you need {notes_50} 50 notes, {notes_20} 20 notes, {notes_10} dd 10 notes and {notes_1} 1' notes)
